  m_PrefabInternal: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1064}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 708705254, guid: f70555f144d8491a825f0804e09c671c, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 0
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
    m_TypeName: UnityEngine.UI.MaskableGraphic+CullStateChangedEvent, UnityEngine.UI,
      Version=1.0.0.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null
  m_FontData:
    m_Font: {fileID: 12800000, guid: 28cd3c84751ca504b992d26fde744e19, type: 3}
    m_FontSize: 31
    m_FontStyle: 0
    m_BestFit: 0
    m_MinSize: 0
    m_MaxSize: 118
    m_Alignment: 1
    m_AlignByGeometry: 1
    m_RichText: 1
    m_HorizontalOverflow: 0
    m_VerticalOverflow: 0
    m_LineSpacing: 1
  m_Text: "Get ready for a bigger, better and more adventurous Raft, improved with
    more features, more content and finally, what you all have been waiting for, Online
    Multiplayer!  Raft will release on Steam Early Access in 2018 so make sure to
    hit the button below and add us to your wishlist to be notified when it launches!\n\n\nWe
    were simply amazed by the love and feedback we got from all of you, and with that
    support we feel we\u2019re able to take Raft to a whole new level. We have taken
    a bigger chunk of time to allow us to implement bigger features, such as multiplayer,
    and make Raft into an even more awesome experience! We are still hard at work
    developing the game and will be for a while longer! We want to ensure the game
    we release will be as good as it can be, which is why we believe it is worth the
    extra time.\n\n\nWe are also pleased to announce that Raft will be published by
    Axolot Games, the developers behind the hugely popular game Scrap Mechanic. When
    we first met with Axolot Games to discuss this cooperation we quickly felt this
    was a perfect match. As they already have a lot of experience and passion for
    survival games, their support will help us turn our, and your, vision for Raft
    into reality. However, it is important to mention that we are still the same team
    working on Raft. This partnership and exchange of ideas will simply strengthen
    both games as we continue development.\n\n\nIn celebration of this announcement,
    both Raft and Scrap Mechanic have some fun stuff in store for you. Raft players
    will be able to find the Scrap Mechanic Duck Trophy to decorate their floating
    home with, while Scrap Mechanic will feature the Shark trophy!\n\n\nSo start brushing
    up on your survival skills and we hope to see you on a raft in 2018! Until then,
    make sure follow us on Steam and the social medias of your choice for more news!\n"
